~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Top Findings
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
1. Workload is dominated by high-concurrency OLTP with periodic Exadata smart-scan assisted reporting.
2. cell single block physical read plus very high flash cache hit volume indicate efficient Exadata storage acceleration.
3. log file sync remains a material bottleneck for commit-heavy transactions despite healthy redo write latency.
4. Row lock contention and cache buffers chains activity suggest hot rows / hot index leaf blocks in order-processing tables.
5. Storage index savings and smart scan return bytes show reporting/batch queries are benefiting from Exadata offload.

